Description: Two joining fragments of body of large North Ionian pottery dinos; interior reserved; exterior much worn with traces of two friezes separated by broad band.
Curator's comments: Probably from same vessel as 1888,0601.393a-f & h

Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 685, no. 435)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1115)
